div.p:
In the next place, We are to conſider Chriſtianity in England,
when divided only into two diſtinct Parties, viz. Proteſtants and
Papiſts, and when the Proteſtants had made a Sub diviſion amongſt
themſelves here. This I take to be in the times of K. Hen. 8.
K. Edw. 6. Q. Mary, and part of the Reign of Q. Elizabeth;
for though there were diverſities of Opinions amongſt Proteſtants,
as well here as in other Countries, even in the firſt beginnings;
yet they were not divided into Parties, being every-where upon
the Defenſive. In the time of K. Hen. 8. which I intend to inſtance
in, both Parties were perſecuted.
